            <bioghist>
                <p>Elizabeth Cadwallader Comfort (1823-1864) was a member of a Quaker family in
                    Bucks County, Pennsylvania. Her parents were Sarah Comfort and Benjamin
                    Cadwallader. In 1845 she married Jeremiah Comfort (1816-1887). Their daughter,
                    Sarah Cadwallader Comfort, was born in 1849. </p>
            </bioghist>

            <scopecontent>
                <p>This is a collection of miscellaneous papers, belonging mostly to Elizabeth
                    Cadwallader Comfort. Materials include: letters (a number addressed to Elizabeth
                    from Sarah Comfort); invitations; school papers; commonplace books (compiled by
                    Rebecca Collins and Rachel Grellet) and miscellaneous quotations; a spiritual
                    journal belonging to Maria Reeve from 1849; a recipe book; and several pieces of
                    personal memorabilia.</p>
            </scopecontent>

